      <hedline>
        <hl1>Big Brother</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jay Williams letter on New York Senate candidate Rick Lazio's position on governmental regulation; says total effect of overegulation is 'grayness' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A May 23 letter lists all sorts of regulations, commissions and statutes of the welfare state that cosset and regulate the contemporary citizen, and wonders if Representative Rick Lazio, who is running for the Senate from New York, would want to do without them.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A May 23 letter lists all sorts of regulations, commissions and statutes of the welfare state that cosset and regulate the contemporary citizen, and wonders if Representative Rick Lazio, who is running for the Senate from New York, would want to do without them.</p>
        <p>Well, the total effect of these products of liberalism and progressivism is that of grayness, a life navigated by some government commission's idea of what is right. Where is the actual person in all this? Alone and overawed by the paternalistic state.</p>
        <p>JAY WILLIAMS  New York, May 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
